&lt;p&gt;PREVOUS APPLICANTS NEED NOT APPLY&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen for an experienced nurse with a passion for infection prevention to join an award winning team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The focus on infection prevention has never been greater and the successful candidate will be expected to provide specialist infection prevention advice and education across the organisation, both in the acute and community settings.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a new permanent position. We are looking to recruit a highly motivated nurse to join an experienced and friendly team that is expanding due to significant recent investment by the trust.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holder will work with the Lead Nurses to ensure that the service meets the demands of our patients and staff both now during what is an unprecedented time and in the months and years to come.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameJohn MannionJob titleLead Nurse Infection PreventionEmail addressjohn.mannion2@nhs.netTelephone number01253 956333&lt;/p&gt;
